        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/14295185-megan?shelf=civil-rights">civil-rights</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/14295185-megan?shelf=deals-with-grief">deals-with-grief</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/14295185-megan?shelf=finding-self">finding-self</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/14295185-megan?shelf=history">history</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/14295185-megan?shelf=feminist-historical-commentary">feminist-historical-commentary</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/14295185-megan?shelf=spiritual">spiritual</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/14295185-megan?shelf=classics">classics</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/14295185-megan?shelf=family-dynamics">family-dynamics</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3665776401" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7987982356120877515">This was a fiery, thought provoking look at the intersection of racism, classism, capitalism and imperialism, how the toxic patriarchy has deliberately created an imperialistic racist political system and plays groups of people against each other. hooks debunks the idea that slavery was harder on Black men or that it emasculated them by going into the horrors and inequalities Black women faced during and after slavery. She reveals the racist, white supremacist underpinnings of the white feminism</span>
  <span id="freeText7987982356120877515" style="display:none">This was a fiery, thought provoking look at the intersection of racism, classism, capitalism and imperialism, how the toxic patriarchy has deliberately created an imperialistic racist political system and plays groups of people against each other. hooks debunks the idea that slavery was harder on Black men or that it emasculated them by going into the horrors and inequalities Black women faced during and after slavery. She reveals the racist, white supremacist underpinnings of the white feminism movement and shows that for real, true change to happen, everyone has to be free, and we have to be working for a society where we hold power cooperatively instead of seeking to mimic the old guard power-over mentality. <br /><br />I wrote down lots and lots of quotes.<br /><br />I highly recommend this excellent book! </span>
