<div id="review_3689404581" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3689404581" />
    <a title="Lilli" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/51623611-lilli"><img alt="Lilli" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1623267171p2/51623611.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3689404581?book_show_action=true">Jul 06, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lilli" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lilli" href="/user/show/51623611-lilli">Lilli</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3689404581" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5339717224429856932">Must read for anyone interested in intersectionality and the racism of the white feminist movement as well as the experience of black women in America. I used this book as a source for various of my essays as it goes into a lot of detail regarding the life experience of black women in America from colonial America to almost present day. It is quite hard to find sources about the lives of enslaved black women as most historical sources focus on either black men or white women, an issue that has b</span>
  <span id="freeText5339717224429856932" style="display:none">Must read for anyone interested in intersectionality and the racism of the white feminist movement as well as the experience of black women in America. I used this book as a source for various of my essays as it goes into a lot of detail regarding the life experience of black women in America from colonial America to almost present day. It is quite hard to find sources about the lives of enslaved black women as most historical sources focus on either black men or white women, an issue that has been very apparent when looking at the feminist movement throughout the 20th century and the fact that white women would often even compare themselves to enslaved black peoples (disregarding black women entirely). bell hooks manages to encapsulate all of these issues in an engaging and accessible way! </span>
  <a data-text-id="5339717224429856932" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


