<div id="review_3427961131" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3427961131" />
    <a title="J" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/756445-j"><img alt="J" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1593394885p2/756445.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3427961131?book_show_action=true">Jul 09, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="J" class="user" itemprop="url" name="J" href="/user/show/756445-j">J</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/756445-j?shelf=anti-racist">anti-racist</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/756445-j?shelf=history">history</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/756445-j?shelf=depressing">depressing</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/756445-j?shelf=politics">politics</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3427961131" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13368344434529198086">This book breaks a lot of myths and stereotypes perpetuated by a racist, patriarchial society about black women, and drives a well-researched arrow towards their bigoted origins. It&apos;s a hard, important book that I wish I had read earlier. My favorite part of this book came in the form a question by Bell Hooks at the end of this book, &quot;How can you be a feminist if you are racist?&quot; She poses this question as to how black women (who may feel excluded by white racists in the women&apos;s movement) should</span>
  <span id="freeText13368344434529198086" style="display:none">This book breaks a lot of myths and stereotypes perpetuated by a racist, patriarchial society about black women, and drives a well-researched arrow towards their bigoted origins. It's a hard, important book that I wish I had read earlier. My favorite part of this book came in the form a question by Bell Hooks at the end of this book, "How can you be a feminist if you are racist?" She poses this question as to how black women (who may feel excluded by white racists in the women's movement) should flip the script. Rather than asking themselves, or other black women, "How can you call yourself a feminist when there are racists in the women's movement?" Hooks responds that people of color, who believe in feminism, should instead ask the racist white women in the movement, "How can you be a feminist if you ignore, dismiss or actively work against women of color on issues of race and class?" It's a brilliant response and this book brought into focus many current controversies within the women's movement and feminist circles, and how they started.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13368344434529198086" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


